REE PIOUS HOPES.     GREETING OF THE INCOMING PRESIDENT TO THE SOCIETY OF AMERICAN ARCHIVISTS ATTHEIR 44TH ANNUAL MEETING, CINCINNATI, OHIO, 3 OCT 80, EXPRESSING 3 'PIOUSHOPES': (1) THAT MEMBERS OF THE SOCIETY WILL VOICE THEIR FEELINGS STRONGLY TOCOUNCIL AND OFFICERS; (2) THAT THE SOCIETY CAN THINK CONSTRUCTIVELY ABOUT THEROLES OF THE PROFESSIONAL STAFF AND ELECTED OFFICERS; AND (3) THAT ATTENDANCEWILL BE GOOD AT THE SOCIETY'S NEXT ANNUAL MEETING IN BERKELEY